<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10477791>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9–12. Habitus of Echinovelleda spp. 9, 10, E. protochinensis Bi & Lin, sp. nov. from Daguan, Yunnan, China; 11, 12, E. mumuae Bi & Mu, sp. nov. from Shizong, Yunnan, China. 9, 11, male; 10, 12, female. 9, holotype; 10–12 paratype. a, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10477791/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10477795>
    dc:description "FIGURES 19–20. Genitalia of Echinovelleda spp. 19, E. protochinensis Bi & Lin, sp. nov.; 20, E. mumuae Bi & Mu, sp. nov. a, tergite VIII with sternites VIII & IX in ventral view; b, tegmen in ventral view and lateral view; c, median lobe in ventral view and lateral view. Scale = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10477795/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10477797>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21–27. Endophallus of Echinovelleda spp. in inflated and everted condition. 21, E. c. chinensis Breuning, 1936; 22, E. c. dichromata Bi, 2018; 23, E. mumuae Bi & Mu, sp. nov.; 24, E. guoliangi (Huang, Huang & Liu, 2020); 25, E. protochinensis Bi & Lin, sp. nov.; 26, E. vitalisi (Pic, 1925); 27, E. qiului (Huang, Huang & Liu, 2020). a, enlargement of apical portion; b apical portion in dorsolateral view. 21, from Bi (2018); 22, from Bi & Chen (2021)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10477797/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

